    <record id="template_imgproxy" model="service.template">
        <field name="name">imgproxy</field>
        <field name="code">imgproxy</field>
        <field name="service_code">imgproxy</field>
        <field name="version">v3.30.1</field>
        <field name="description">imgproxy is a fast and secure standalone server for resizing, processing, and converting images on the fly.</field>
        <field name="rich_description"><![CDATA[<div class="agz-app-desc">
  <p class="agz-app-lead">imgproxy is a fast and secure standalone server for resizing, processing, and converting images on the fly.</p>
  <p>Written in Go on top of the libvips library, imgproxy fetches a source image from your own storage and applies transformations encoded directly in the request URL, returning an optimized result. It offloads all image-processing work from your application, so your backend only needs to generate signed URLs. It is built on three principles: simplicity, speed, and security, and ships as Docker images and Linux packages.</p>
  <h6 class="agz-app-subhead">Key features</h6>
  <ul class="agz-app-feats">
    <li>On-the-fly resizing, cropping, rotating, watermarking, and filters via URL options</li>
    <li>Broad format support including JPEG, PNG, GIF, WebP, AVIF, and JPEG XL</li>
    <li>Optimization with metadata and color-profile stripping, PNG quantization, and auto-quality</li>
    <li>Signed URLs to prevent denial-of-service and unauthorized transformation requests</li>
    <li>Image-bomb protection that checks real dimensions before processing</li>
    <li>Reads sources from local disk, HTTP, S3-compatible object storage, Google Cloud Storage, and Azure Blob</li>
  </ul>
  <h6 class="agz-app-subhead">Best for</h6>
  <p>Teams and platforms that serve user-generated or catalog imagery and want to replace pre-generated thumbnails with secure, on-demand processing, typically placed behind a CDN or reverse proxy that handles HTTP caching.</p>
</div>]]></field>
        <field name="category">media</field>
        <field name="is_web_app">True</field>
        <field name="requires_database">False</field>
        <field name="requires_backup">True</field>
